		<div class="comment-body"><p>A lot depends on location. I own 2 .270 rifles and a .357 levergun with matching revlolver. I have given the situation much thought and if I HAD to bug out the levergun would be my main defense arm. That being said nothing beats a single shot 12 or 20 ga for food gathering. I grew up with a single shot 20 and what a versatile gun. I am an avid grouse hunter and have taken them with a Ruger 10/22 and also a 20ga. The shotgun wins out every time. When I need to eat my single shot &#8220;boom stick&#8221; never lets me down. Tie one to the side of your pack.. A box of shells will go a long way.</p>
